¶ ⦊
  ‖ \ssection{Why} ⦉

  ‖ A point in the plane can be ‹interpreted› as a
    ‹displacement›. ⦉
⦉

¶ ⦊
  ‖ \ssection{Definition} ⦉

  ‖ A ❬plane vector❭ (or ❬vector❭, ❬two-dimensional vector❭,
    ❬2-vector❭) is an element of $𝗥^2$. ⦉

  ‖ We associate a list of two numbers with a point in the
    plane, a ‹location›. ⦉

  ‖ We also associate a list of two numbers with a
    ‹displacement›, a ‹change› in location. ⦉
⦉

