¶ ⦊
  ‖ \ssubsection{Note on terminology} ⦉

  ‖ The English word “vector” is from the same Latin word
    “vector,” meaning, literally, carrier. ⦉

  ‖ This sense is from the interpretation of a vector as
    indicating a displacement. ⦉
